Ad Text:
Digital Cost Analyst

Perth CBD based role.

Hybrid Setup (3 days office, 2 days wfh)

6 months contract




The Cost Analyst for the Digital team plays a key role in developing tools, processes, and frameworks that promote financial transparency and governance across the entire Digital portfolio. This position is critical in supporting informed decision-making by delivering clear insights into budget allocations, actual expenditures, and overall financial performance.

Duties & Responsibilities

Financial Visibility & Reporting: Develop tools and frameworks to provide clear, end-to-end visibility of Digital budgets, including variance analysis and forecasting across business units.

Cost Attribution & Governance: Implement processes to attribute Digital and cloud costs across business areas, ensuring transparency, compliance, and alignment with financial policies.

Dashboards & Analytics: Build and maintain user-friendly Power BI dashboards for tracking budgets, project financials, and cost drivers, enabling self-serve analytics and financial transparency.

Forecasting & Optimization: Support regular forecasting cycles, conduct variance root-cause analysis, and identify opportunities for cost efficiency and optimization.

Governance & Compliance Support: Ensure adherence to financial governance standards, assist with audits, and support cost recovery efforts across Digital services and assets.




Skills & Experience

Strong analytical and financial modeling skills with high attention to detail

Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication abilities

Strategic mindset with a focus on process improvement and cost optimization

Proficient in Power BI or similar analytics tools

Knowledge of FinOps or cloud cost management (preferred)


What you need to do now

If you're interested in this role, click 'apply now' to forward an up-to-date copy of your CV

If this job isn't quite right for you, but you are looking for a new position, please contact us for a confidential discussion about your career.

Email: caryl.isuan@airswift.com   

Mobile: +61 8 6318 1100 




Airswift is an international workforce solutions provider.  With 1000 employees and 9,000 contractors operating in over 70 countries, Airswift's geographical reach, experience, and expertise across the energy, mining, infrastructure, and technology sectors is unparalleled. 

By joining Airswift's community you gain exclusive access to our candidate portal 'Airswift Digital'. First-release features include early notification of upcoming assignments via automated matching, access to our digital timesheet portal, and exclusive access to content designed to support your career development. 

At Airswift, we are passionate about providing equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity to benefit all. We actively encourage applications from any background.

ALG Talent is currently seeking experienced Data Analysts to join one of Australia's leading commercial airlines based at Brisbane Airport. This is an opportunity for candidates who can hit the ground running and make an immediate impact.

This is a casual position working full-time office hours, offering an initial minimum 3-month contract with strong potential for extension.



Reports to: Head of Procurement and Part Sales

Purpose:
The Data Analyst - Freight & Logistics is responsible for collecting, analysing and interpreting data across freight, logistics and supply chain operations. The role delivers actionable insights to streamline processes, improve efficiency, reduce costs and support strategic decision-making. The analyst works closely with cross-functional teams to ensure data-driven improvements in financial and operational performance.

Key Responsibilities:

The Data Analyst is responsible for but not limited to:
Rapidly collect, cleanse and integrate freight and logistics data from multiple sources.
Analyse shipment details, costs, carrier performance and delivery metrics to identify quick wins and urgent opportunities.
Conduct focused lane-level cost analysis, route optimisation, and carrier benchmarking to support immediate decision-making.
Build and deliver predictive models for demand, shipment volumes, and lead times, tailored to current business priorities.
Present clear, concise findings and recommendations to stakeholders for fast implementation.
Collaborate with procurement, logistics, finance, and operations teams to ensure alignment and accelerate improvements.
Ensure all work complies with company policies, safety, security, and regulatory requirements.


Key Deliverables:

Cost Optimisation Analysis: Targeted analysis identifying immediate cost drivers, savings opportunities and prioritised recommendations for process improvements.
Forecasting Models: Developed predictive analytics for shipment volumes, demand, and lead times, with clear documentation of assumptions and accuracy.
Performance Dashboards: Simple, actionable dashboards or reports tracking key metrics and trends for ongoing monitoring by the business.


Qualifications:

Bachelor's degree in Logistics, Supply Chain Management, Data Science or related field.
Proven experience as a Data Analyst in logistics, freight or supply chain environment.
Advanced skills in Excel, SQL, Power BI/Tableau, Python/R and data visualisation.


Knowledge & Experience:

Strong understanding of logistics operations, freight management, and supply chain principles.
Familiar with industry KPIs, compliance standards and best practices.


Skills:

Analytical and problem-solving mindset.
Effective communicator across technical and non-technical audiences.
Ability to work collaboratively in cross-functional teams.
Attention to detail and strong organisational skills.

What you’ll be working on

Working with the Fleet team and reporting to the Senior Manager Vehicles and Ground Support Equipment, you will develop and implement operational plans and programs and assist in fleet planning, system reporting, or fleet development and planning projects with the objective to ensure service and operations excellence, increase revenue and enhance customer experience with the objective to achieve FedEx productivity and service goals.

Analyse vehicle and ground support equipment fleet operational and maintenance data across the APAC region.
Develop and review fleet usage and assist with building operating plans to attain service and productivity goals.
Administration of vehicle and equipment operational telemetric systems.
Assist with interpreting asset technical specifications across the existing fleets and with new technologies, including electric vehicles, that help FedEx meet our sustainability goals for reducing carbon emissions. 
Work with project teams for introducing new assets, including new technology vehicles and equipment, as well as the associated infrastructure for electric vehicles.
Ensure that all safety, operational, and compliance requirements are adhered to. 
Interpret data on historical trends of fleet costs, conduct operational and cost impact analysis for new programs/services and market/operational expansion. 
Analyse, recommend and implement ways to improve service and cost performance within the responsible area, research, and benchmark best practices.
Identify needs, develop, and implement contingency plans within the service areas for crisis management or long-term usage in order to minimize risks, costs and operational impact to APAC operations and protect FedEx’s employees and properties.

Location: Sydney area

What you’ll bring to the team

Bachelor degree in Industrial Engineering, Systems Engineering, Computer Science, or related discipline.
Advanced level proficiency with Power BI, MS Excel. 
Programming / coding / data analytical skills including SQL data base queries, and Python.
Demonstrated analytical, conceptual, and planning skills.
Relevant computer modelling skills preferred.
Proven ability to work collaboratively within a team environment as well as autonomously when required.
Excellent communication skills and the ability to communicate effectively at all levels from frontline to senior managers and directors.

FedEx was built on a philosophy that puts people first, one we take seriously. We are an equal opportunity/affirmative action employer and we are committed to a diverse, equitable, and inclusive workforce in which we enforce fair treatment, and provide growth opportunities for everyone.

All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment regardless of age, race, color, national origin, genetics, religion, gender, marital status, pregnancy (including childbirth or a related medical condition), physical or mental disability, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations, and ordinances.

Our Company

FedEx is one of the world's largest express transportation companies and has consistently been selected as one of the top 10 World’s Most Admired Companies by "Fortune" magazine. Every day FedEx delivers for its customers with transportation and business solutions, serving more than 220 countries and territories around the globe. We can serve this global network due to our outstanding team of FedEx team members, who are tasked with making every FedEx experience outstanding.

Our Philosophy

The People-Service-Profit philosophy (P-S-P) describes the principles that govern every FedEx decision, policy, or activity. FedEx takes care of our people; they, in turn, deliver the impeccable service demanded by our customers, who reward us with the profitability necessary to secure our future. The essential element in making the People-Service-Profit philosophy such a positive force for the company is where we close the circle, and return these profits back into the business, and invest back in our people. Our success in the industry is attributed to our people. Through our P-S-P philosophy, we have a work environment that encourages team members to be innovative in delivering the highest possible quality of service to our customers. We care for their well-being, and value their contributions to the company.

Our Culture

Our culture is important for many reasons, and we intentionally bring it to life through our behaviors, actions, and activities in every part of the world. The FedEx culture and values have been a cornerstone of our success and growth since we began in the early 1970’s. While other companies can copy our systems, infrastructure, and processes, our culture makes us unique and is often a differentiating factor as we compete and grow in today’s global marketplace.

Job Title: Lead Enterprise Portfolio Specialist - Enterprise Portfolio Management Office
Category:
Programme & Project Management (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - Federal (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Shape enterprise portfolio management, governance and reporting at one of Australia's most iconic institutions
Sydney-based hybrid work environment


ABOUT THE TEAM

The Enterprise Strategy and Change Department enables the Reserve Bank of Australia to deliver on its Corporate Plan by coordinating enterprise strategic planning and portfolio management, delivering IT-enabled change, and embedding a continuous improvement capability.


As part of this department, the Enterprise Portfolio Management Office (EPMO) is a centralised function responsible for providing effective governance over the Bank's strategic investment portfolio. Our objectives are to strengthen project management practices, provide assurance and oversight across the Bank's portfolio and guide improved project governance and delivery. We support the evaluation, prioritisation, and ongoing monitoring of the Bank's portfolio of projects and initiatives. We also provide advice and support to the Bank's senior stakeholders and governance groups.


ABOUT THE ROLE

The Lead Enterprise Portfolio Specialist will report to the Manager - Portfolio Planning & Insights to support enterprise-wide portfolio planning and prioritisation and the ongoing management, governance and reporting on the Bank's portfolio of projects and initiatives to senior stakeholders and governance groups.


As the Lead Enterprise Portfolio Specialist, you will:


Partner with senior leaders and work collaboratively with stakeholders across business units to shape and deliver enterprise portfolio planning, prioritisation and management aligned to the Bank's longer-term direction.
Lead the evaluation, prioritisation and sequencing of the Bank's enterprise projects and initiatives to achieve the Bank's Corporate Plan and demonstrate the value of the EPMO in achieving organisational goals.
Facilitate enterprise planning and prioritisation workshops with senior leaders across the Bank.
Conduct structured analysis and research to generate insights, test hypotheses, and inform strategic decision-making.
Support and engage with executives, committees, and governance bodies through high-quality communication (verbal and written) and strategic narrative/ story-telling.
Lead the application and evolution of the Bank's portfolio prioritisation framework to support strategic decision making, ensuring it is fit for purpose and meets the ongoing needs of the Bank.
Provide timely assessment of portfolio performance, as well as early identification of and options for resolution of portfolio-level risks and issues impacting the portfolio.
Provide transparency and produce high quality portfolio analysis and timely reports including portfolio/ thematic insights and recommendations that support the Bank's decision makers and ensure portfolio governance reporting requirements are met to a high standard.
Provide accurate and timely information to enable strategic decisions on the Bank's portfolio of work based on a clear understanding of cost, risk, resourcing, impacts and business benefits/ outcomes.
Contribute to the development of innovative enterprise solutions to complex organisational challenges that support the Bank's long-term strategic direction.
Review and evaluate, including providing recommendations on, new Business Cases and Seed Funding/ Change Requests, ensuring quality submissions are made to the Investment Committee and support portfolio level decision making.
Help build a high-performing, values-led EPMO that drives clarity, alignment, and impact across the enterprise.
Support continuous improvement initiatives within the EPMO, working collaboratively to embed improvement practices and uplift capability.
Support Secretariat activities for the Investment Committee.


ABOUT YOU

You are a strategic thinker and collaborative problem solver with a passion for driving meaningful change. You bring:


Experience & Expertise


Minimum 8+ years' experience in enterprise portfolio planning, prioritisation, management, governance and reporting in large, complex institutions.
Minimum 3 years in strategy / management consulting role at Manager level or equivalent (e.g. Big Four, Tier 1.5, MBB); strong consulting toolkit.
Experience in financial services or public sector environments (highly regarded).
Proven strategic portfolio analytical capabilities, with the ability to synthesise data, build models (e.g. financial, economic, strategic, decision-making, performance, process).
Experience in applying and evolving enterprise planning and prioritisation frameworks.
Experience in developing thematic/ strategic insights and recommendations for senior stakeholders and governance groups aligned with organisational objectives and review/ evaluate business cases.
Proven ability to translate strategy into actionable plans and measurable outcomes.
Experience in facilitating/ supporting executive-level engagements and delivery of organisation priorities with a focus on outcomes.
Excellent stakeholder engagement/ management and communication skills (verbal and written).
Knowledge of portfolio/ project management methodologies, frameworks, techniques and tools is highly desirable.
Experience with Data Analytics tools (e.g. PowerBI) and Work Management tools (e.g. JIRA) is highly desirable.


Skills & Capabilities

Proficient at synthesizing a variety of information and data into insights, options, and recommendations.
Excellent communication skills (verbal, written, and visual) with the ability to influence and engage across all levels.
Strong planning and prioritisation workshop design and facilitation skills.
Ability to work autonomously and collaboratively in a high-performing team.
Comfortable navigating ambiguity, learning and adapting quickly, and delivering results in a dynamic environment.
Understanding of financial services regulation, compliance, and institutional accountability (highly regarded).


Qualifications

Tertiary qualifications in Business, Finance, Economics, Engineering, or a related discipline.
Postgraduate qualifications, e.g. MBA (highly regarded).
Certifications in Human-Centred Design, Design Thinking, Agile, Lean Six Sigma, or Project/Program Management (e.g. PRINCE2, MSP, PMI) are highly desirable.
Certifications in related disciplines or Project/Program Management (e.g. PRINCE2, MSP, PMI) are advantageous but not mandatory.


BE MORE
Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.


WHY RBA?
The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people. Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go.


Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts. We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.


The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

Exposure to AI/ML concepts and ability to design for future advanced analytics use cases.

Here’s how you will make a difference in this role…

Embracing our value of Everyone Matters we hold a collective commitment to foster an environment where all differences are valued and respected. 

We encourage individuals from all backgrounds including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, those caring for someone or living with a disability, LGBTQIA+ and culturally diverse applicants to apply.

We embrace hybrid working and welcome conversations about flexibility. 

Please note all successful candidates will undergo background checks (including criminal history and ASIC checks) and an NDIS Workers Screening Check if appropriate.  All information provided will be treated confidentially. 

We acknowledge Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples as the Traditional Custodians of the lands where we live, learn and work.

Job Title: Senior Quantitative Analyst // Market Risk Model
Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Salary: Discuss with recruiter about the rate
Ad Text:
Our client is seeking a Senior Quantitative Analyst with strong Market Risk Model & C++ experienceexperience to join their project team on an initial 12-month contract. This role will focus on the development, validation, enhancement, and support of market risk models used across trading and risk management functions.

The successful candidate will work closely with Risk, Front Office, Technology, and Model Governance teams to ensure market risk models are robust, compliant, and aligned with regulatory and business requirements.

This role will start in late Feb 2026.


Responsibilities
Develop, enhance, and maintain market risk models, including VaR, Stressed VaR, Expected Shortfall, sensitivities, and stress testing frameworks.

Perform model validation, back-testing, benchmarking, and ongoing performance monitoring.

Analyse market data, model assumptions, and limitations to ensure models remain fit for purpose.

Support regulatory and internal model reviews, including documentation, audit responses, and remediation activities.

Collaborate with trading desks, risk managers, and technology teams to implement model changes and improvements.

Provide expert quantitative input into risk methodologies, capital calculations, and scenario analysis.

Produce clear, concise documentation and present findings to senior stakeholders and governance forums.

Assist with incident investigations and remediation related to model or data issues.

Requirements
Proven experience as a Senior Quantitative Analyst within Market Risk (A MUST)

Strong hands-on experience with market risk models (e.g., VaR, Expected Shortfall, stress testing).

Solid understanding of financial instruments across equities, fixed income, FX, and derivatives.

Experience with model validation, back-testing, and governance processes.

Strong programming skills in C++ (A MUST)

Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills.

Ability to work independently in a contract role while collaborating effectively with multiple stakeholders.

Degree (or higher) in Mathematics, Statistics, Quantitative Finance, Engineering, or a related discipline.

Postgraduate qualification (e.g., MSc, PhD) or professional certifications (FRM, CFA) highly regarded.




If you think you have the above skills and experiences, click the 'Apply' button or send your resume to alex.nguyen@talentinternational.com

Job Title: Principal Consultant - Data and Analytics | Brisbane
Ad Text:
Our Purpose

As a Principal Consultant, you will lead the technical delivery of large-scale data platform and BI solutions. You will be asked to design, implement and own the delivery of robust Data Platform solutions and end-to-end components. This is a client facing role, so you'll need to be an excellent communicator and good with people. The Principal Consultant works closely with practice leads, project managers, scrum masters, and client stakeholders and teams.

What You’ll Do

Working with clients (businesses users) to gather, clarify requirements and business rules by running workshops with stakeholders.
Lead the technical architecture, design and delivery for a new Data platform.
Provide overall thought leadership to our clients regarding data profiling and integration recommendations.
Data modelling (relational and dimensional like star schema and Snowflake schema)
Managing development life cycle using various source code management tools.
Ability to perform performance tuning and optimisation on new and/or existing data warehouse solutions.
Provide detailed documentation, end user training and knowledge-transfer services to customers, and internal teams.
Mentor developers, acting as an SME in data warehouse architecture and data modelling

What You’ll Bring:

Advanced data modelling skills (Star schema, Snowflake schema, data vault)
Proven track-record of building EDW’s
Advanced ETL /ELT processes design and implementation.
Advanced skills in performance tuning, query plan, query plan analysis, indexing, table partitioning.
Strong skills in cloud platforms such as Azure, AWS & GCP
Strong skills in Azure Data Factory and data Flows  and Azure SQL data platform.
Extensive knowledge of Databricks architecture and features.
Proven track-record  in the design, development and implementation of data solutions using Databricks.
Extensive knowledge of Snowflake’s architecture and features.
Proven track-record  in the design, development and implementation of data solutions using Snowflake.
Experience in data ingestion tools such as Apache Kafka, Informatica, AWS Glue, Azure event hubs, Fivetran, Matillion, DBT and Coalesce.
Experience in Apache Airflow.
Strong consultation and clients’ management skills
Strong understanding of Agile delivery methodology.
Excellent verbal and written communications.

 

Required Skills and Qualifications

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related discipline
Minimum 8+ years’ experience in EDW design and implementation.
Minimum 8+ years’ experience in ETL architecting and design.
Minimum 8+ years’ experience in data modelling (Star schema & Snowflake schema)
Minimum 5+ years’ experience in semantic layer development.
Minimum 5+ years’ experience in reporting and visualization tools.
Advanced skills in Microsoft BI stack.
Minimum 8+ years’ experience in various Microsoft SQL server technologies including SSIS, SSRS, SSAS
Minimum 4+ years’ experience in design, development and implementation of data solutions using Snowflake.
Minimum 4+ years’ experience in design, development and implementation of data solutions using Databricks.
Wherescape RED, 3D experience is preferred.
Minimum 3+ years’ experience in Power BI.
Advanced skills in Azure, Fabric, and Snowflake pipelines, with experience in tools such as Azure Data Factory, Coalesce, Matillion, dbt, and Fivetran.
Strong skills in data platform implementation, configuration, performance and cost management tuning (i.e. Azure, Fabric, Snowflake).

 

Why join us here at Datacom?

Datacom is one of Australia and New Zealand’s largest suppliers of Information Technology professional services. We have managed to maintain a dynamic, agile, small business feel that is often diluted in larger organisations of our size. It's our people that give Datacom its unique culture and energy that you can feel from the moment you meet with us.

We care about our people and provide a range of perks such as social events, chill-out spaces, remote working, flexi-hours and professional development courses to name a few. You’ll have the opportunity to learn, develop your career, connect and bring your true self to work. You will be recognised and valued for your contributions and be able to do your work in a collegial, flat-structured environment.

We operate at the forefront of technology to help Australia and New Zealand’s largest enterprise organisations explore possibilities and solve their greatest challenges, so you will never run out of interesting new challenges and opportunities.

We want Datacom to be an inclusive and welcoming workplace for everyone and take pride in the steps we have taken and continue to take to make our environment fun and friendly, and our people feel supported.

Job Title: Principal Data Consultant

Strong technical knowledge across modern data platforms — Azure, AWS, Databricks, Snowflake (one or more required).

Job Title: I.T Snr Business Analyst (D365 Supply Chain & Ops)
Ad Text:
About us:
Snackbrands Australia is part of Intersnack Group, a private German snack food company founded in 1968. Although internationally owned we are still very much a local company Creating Happy Snacking Moments for everyone!


Here at Snack Brands Australia, we proudly make some of Australia’s favourite snacks including Kettle, CC’s, Thins, Cheezels, The Natural Chip Company and Nice & Natural. Across our three sites, we make over 200 million packets of chips a year - that's a lot of enjoyment and fun we bring to snackers every day! We encourage a culture that is exciting, challenging and we strive for innovation in everything we do. Our aim is for our people to share in our success, enjoy our products and reap the benefits of their hard work within a supportive environment where work life balance is encouraged!


About the role:


We’re looking for an experienced Senior Business Analyst – Supply Chain Management to join our IT Applications team and drive the successful delivery of D365 projects, enhancements and support across our Operations function.

This role will be based between our head office in Norwest with regular travel to our manufacturing site at Orchard Hills.

What you’ll be responsible for:

Lead analysis, configuration and delivery of Microsoft D365 Operations projects and enhancements
Support supply chain and manufacturing users including production problems, incidents and change requests i.e. manage and resolve open tickets in your support queue.
Follow ITIL processes and methodologies for approval and migration of changes to production
Collaborate with Operations, Project Office and IT teams to resolve issues across operations, manufacturing, warehousing, distribution and inventory.
Partner with supply chain and operations departments across the business to ensure solutions meet operational requirements and align with business milestones.
Coordinate project plans, budgets and reporting.
Influence best practice solution architecture and support a high-performance IT culture.
Work with vendors to provide support and upgrade information.
Develop, execute and lead unit, system and user testing as required to implement changes into production
Build strong relationships across stakeholders and business users. 

What you’ll bring to the role:
Proven experience as a Senior BA in Supply Chain/SCM, ideally in FMCG.
Excellent Dynamics 365 and business process knowledge in the Manufacturing and Supply Chain modules.
Solution knowledge of Dynamics 365, SQL data base and integration technologies.
Excellent communication, stakeholder engagement and influencing skills.
Strong analytical, project planning and commercial acumen.
Ability to manage multiple initiatives, navigate conflicting priorities and work with senior leaders 


What can you expect in return?
A supportive working environment (with plenty of snacks on hand!) where you'll feel engaged and valued, career growth, Birthday Leave, Access to discounts on Retailers, onsite parking (including electric car charging stations) and a focus on health and wellness (like Wellbeing Days!) to make your workplace more enjoyable!

You’ll partner closely with leaders across the business to embed AI into real products and services, turning ideas into measurable outcomes. As the function grows, you’ll continuously optimise models, lift performance, and evolve capability at pace.

CPB Contractors is Australia’s leading contractor and the largest infrastructure construction company in our region. Part of the CIMIC Group, we are proud to be constructing Australia’s future and do so collaboratively with our partners and clients.

We hire for careers, not project life. CPB Contractors has more than 50 major infrastructure projects in delivery, across all key sectors of the construction industry, including roads and bridges, rail, tunnelling, defence, airports, buildings and resources, providing you with career opportunities for years to come.

What can our construction projects build for you?

CPB Contractors along with our industry partners has been selected as preferred proponent to deliver two major packages for the Cross River Rail Projects: the Tunnel, Stations and Development (TSD) package and the Rail, Integration and Systems (RIS) package. Cross River Rail is a new 10.2-kilometre rail line from Dutton Park to Bowen Hills, which includes 5.9 kilometres of tunnel under the Brisbane River and the CBD.

The RIS package is crucial to the overall delivery and success of Cross River Rail, and its integration with the Queensland Rail network.  RIS will be delivered by the UNITY Alliance which brings CPB Contractors, UGL, AECOM and Jacobs together with partners HASSEL, RCS Australia, Acmena, Martinus Rail and WIRED Overhead Solutions to deliver the full scope of works over the next five years. This includes:

Rail civil and electrical works
Brownfield rail surface works primarily to the north of the tunnel, including an upgrade of Exhibition Station and a major augmentation of Mayne Yard
Upgrade of seven suburban stations to the south
Rail operational systems works
Rail signalling works and communication, and integration and commission activities.

Your opportunity

Reporting into the Finance Manager, this role will sit in the project finance team with access to a broad range of finance and operational systems and staff. This role will analyse data from the projects ERP, BI and operational systems and develop meaningful insights for stakeholders across all levels.

Responsibilities will include:

Review of forecasting model to ensure that the UNITY forecast is consolidated in a robust platform, minimising calculation and data errors
Engage with stakeholders to improve their cost reporting and forecasting
Assist in preparing papers for review and approval by the Alliance Leadership Team
Papers are to set out details of spend, forecast and reasons for the project claiming the costs against the Project Owner
Assist in month end activities, primarily assisting with cost reviews to identify and correct any costs that are not reimbursable
Support the Finance Manager with ad-hoc reporting requests

Our minimum requirements for this role are:

Degree qualified in Commerce / Business majoring in Accounting and/or Finance
CA / CPA qualification desirable but not mandatory
Minimum 2 years working in an FP&A / Business Partnering role or similar
Experience working in a large Construction / Engineering / Infrastructure / Property business
Systems experience especially with BI platforms. Recent hands-on experience with BI/JDE an advantage but not mandatory
Advanced Excel and (user friendly) modelling skills
Ability to structure complex data from a variety of sources to develop insights for executive level management
Proven ability to drive process improvements and automation not just in a Finance environment but at an operations / project level
Natural ability to business partner with non-finance teams and build strong relationships
Analytical and inquisitive nature and a desire to always challenge the norm
Commercially savvy with business acumen
Flexible and adaptable to a fast paced and changing environment
Ability to work autonomously and is self-motivated
Strong sense of ethics and values
Experience working hands-on in a project environment desirable but not mandatory
Experience with preparing (or assisting with) budgets / forecasts for large businesses desirable but not mandatory
Experience working in Big 4 / mid-tier accounting firms desirable but not mandatory

 

We particularly welcome and encourage applications from Indigenous Peoples, women, the LGBTQIA+ community, mature workers, Veterans and Active Defence Reserve members, people with disabilities and people from different cultural backgrounds. CPB Contractors is proud to hold the Workplace Gender Equality Agency (WGEA) Citation - Employer of Choice for Gender Equality.

We’re always looking for ways to make CPB Contractors a more rewarding place to work and offer a unique set of benefits, including:

A rewarding career where we support your development, training and promote from within.
Opportunities across all construction sectors so that there is always an opportunity suitable for the next stage in your career.
Competitive remuneration and excellent benefits including a health and wellbeing program, discount portal and company-funded salary continuance insurance.
Flexible work arrangements and a culture that values diversity and innovation.

Please note: This role is being sourced through CPB Contractors directly and we will not accept applications via external recruitment agencies.

There's No Us Without U. Care with Us, for Today and Tomorrow

There's no life without water, and at Urban Utilities, we live and breathe that knowledge every single day. It's why our people are so passionate about what they do and how they do it. And it's why we need people like YOU. Come shape our future with us and make a real and lasting impact across our teams.

Your Opportunity

We have an opportunity in a newly shaped Strategic Asset Data Analyst role in our Infrastructure Planning & Delivery group.

This role sits in our Integrated Planning team, who are essential in shaping the vision and objectives of our policies and servicing strategies. The team is responsible for building, adapting, and implementing plans for catchments, water supply zones, and data systems to define performance targets, establish investment pathways, and develop Strategic Business Cases - all driving an affordable, sustainable, and deliverable portfolio to achieve key objectives.

Reporting to the Leader Strategic Asset Planning, the Strategic Asset Data Analyst supports the design, configuration, testing and application of advanced analytics tools and systems for renewal investment forecasting and asset management as part of the asset planning team.

The Strategic Asset Data Analyst is responsible for utilising engineering and data science, combined with technical asset management knowledge to leverage big data and business intelligence tools to deliver real impact for Urban Utilities.

Some of your accountabilities will include:

Undertake strategic and tactical investment planning scenario analysis and modelling over a 10 - 100-year horizon to enable asset planning and support delivery of our critical outcomes.
Make recommendations to improve data and analytics systems and platforms, contributing to the continuous improvement and refinement of data and analytics strategy.

Why Urban Utilities?

At Urban Utilities, the work we do is about so much more than the bottom line. We're a leading provider of world-class drinking water and wastewater services to the vibrant communities of Brisbane, Ipswich, Lockyer Valley, Somerset, and Scenic Rim. As we continue to grow, we're committed to planning ahead and shaping a sustainable future around water for generations to come.

At the core of our work lies genuine care: for our team, our customers, communities, and the environment. From the flush of a toilet to major infrastructure projects and residential developments, we're dedicated to being there every step of the way.

Our HQ is in Fortitude Valley, Brisbane, but you'll find us all over SEQ - working in cool places like the SAS Laboratory in Darra, field-based depots in Eagle Farm, Acacia Ridge, Bundamba, and wastewater treatment plants dotted across the region.
